WEBVTT

00:00:02.730 --> 00:00:04.770
<i>Wealth, fame, power...</i>

00:00:04.770 --> 00:00:06.670
<i>Gold Roger,
the King of the Pirates,</i>

00:00:06.670 --> 00:00:08.970
<i>attained everything
this world has to offer.</i>

00:00:08.970 --> 00:00:12.840
<i>The words he uttered just before
his death drove people to the seas.</i>

00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:16.680
<i>My treasure? If you want it,
you can have it!</i>

00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:20.240
<i>Find it! I left everything
this world has to offer there!</i>

00:00:22.850 --> 00:00:27.590
<i>And so men head for the Grand Line
in pursuit of their dreams!</i>

00:00:27.590 --> 00:00:31.490
<i>The world has truly entered
a Great Pirate Era!</i>

00:00:31.490 --> 00:00:36.860
<i>We're going to gather up
all our dreams</i>

00:00:36.860 --> 00:00:42.770
<i>and set out in search
of something to find</i>

00:00:42.770 --> 00:00:44.100
<i>ONE PIECE!</i>

00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:54.620
<i>Compasses only cause delays</i>

00:00:54.620 --> 00:01:00.350
<i>Delirious with fever,
I take the helm</i>

00:01:00.350 --> 00:01:10.350
<i>If the dusty treasure map has
been verified, it's not a legend!</i>

00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:18.170
<i>When it comes to personal storms,</i>

00:01:18.170 --> 00:01:23.480
<i>simply ride aboard
someone else's biorhythm</i>

00:01:23.480 --> 00:01:27.150
<i>and pretend it isn't there!</i>

00:01:27.150 --> 00:01:32.650
<i>We're going to gather up
all our dreams</i>

00:01:32.650 --> 00:01:38.360
<i>and set out in search
of something to find</i>

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:44.600
<i>A coin in my pocket,
and do you wanna be my friend?</i>

00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:49.970
<i>We are, We are on the cruise!</i>

00:01:49.970 --> 00:01:51.040
<i>We are!</i>

00:02:06.090 --> 00:02:07.680
Fire!

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:19.530
What are you-?!

00:02:19.530 --> 00:02:21.240
<i>Luffy-san!</i>

00:02:21.240 --> 00:02:22.860
Straw Hat?!

00:02:28.340 --> 00:02:31.340
That doesn't work!

00:02:35.580 --> 00:02:38.920
I told you I was strong!

00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:42.420
W-who the hell are you?!

00:02:42.420 --> 00:02:44.030
I'm Luffy!

00:02:44.030 --> 00:02:47.290
The man who's gonna
be King of the Pirates!

00:02:47.290 --> 00:02:56.030
"Morgan vs. Luffy!
Who's the Mysterious Pretty Girl?"

00:02:57.270 --> 00:03:01.410
W-what?!
The King of the Pirates?!

00:03:01.410 --> 00:03:05.110
Do you even know
what that means?!

00:03:05.110 --> 00:03:07.550
King of the Pirates
is King of the Pirates!

00:03:07.550 --> 00:03:09.610
Are there any other meanings?

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:13.650
I was shocked, too!

00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:17.220
<i>But Luffy-san is serious!
That's how he is!</i>

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:19.230
He intends to become
the King of the Pirates

00:03:19.230 --> 00:03:23.930
and obtain this world's ultimate
treasure... the One Piece!

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:29.800
Here's your treasure!

00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:33.540
Which is yours? I couldn't tell,
so I brought three of 'em.

00:03:33.540 --> 00:03:35.680
All three are mine.

00:03:35.680 --> 00:03:38.010
I use the Three-Sword Style.

00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:41.150
You'll take 'em, right?

00:03:41.150 --> 00:03:43.150
If we fight together now,

00:03:43.150 --> 00:03:45.490
you'll be
a government-defying villain!

00:03:45.490 --> 00:03:49.460
Would you prefer that, or being
killed by the navy like this?

00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:51.690
What are you, the devil's son?!

00:03:51.690 --> 00:03:53.030
Well, whatever.

00:03:53.030 --> 00:03:57.830
I'll be your pirate,
if I'm just gonna die here instead!

00:03:57.830 --> 00:04:01.500
Hurray! So you'll join my crew?!

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:04.040
Alright! Woo-hoo!
This is great! Alright!

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:07.340
Okay! Now untie these
stupid ropes already!

00:04:07.340 --> 00:04:08.940
What... is he?

00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:11.350
He flung the bullets back!

00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:13.950
He's no ordinary human,
that Straw Hat...

00:04:13.950 --> 00:04:17.490
Must've eaten one of those
rumored Devil Fruits!

00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:20.480
--A Devil Fruit?!
--The hidden treasures of the sea?!

00:04:22.590 --> 00:04:24.560
The Devil Fruits...

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:29.220
Whoever eats one is said to gain
seemingly unworldly abilities.

00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:33.300
The power to breathe fire...

00:04:33.300 --> 00:04:35.600
The power to cause tsunamis...

00:04:35.600 --> 00:04:37.670
There are all sorts of rumors,

00:04:37.670 --> 00:04:41.610
but there are many types, and
almost nothing is known about them.

00:04:41.610 --> 00:04:46.350
It's said the secrets to
them lie in the Grand Line...

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:51.320
...but there's no question Straw
Hat just displayed a devil power!

00:04:51.320 --> 00:04:52.920
Hurry! Hurry!

00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:55.160
Damn! These knots are tight!

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:56.960
Hey! Quit wastin' time!

00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:58.790
<i>No matter who they are,</i>

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:01.430
everyone who opposes
me gets executed!

00:05:01.430 --> 00:05:03.950
If guns won't work,
then chop them to death!

00:05:07.970 --> 00:05:10.640
Huh, that's weird!
It got tighter instead!

00:05:10.640 --> 00:05:12.470
Give me a damn sword!

00:05:15.410 --> 00:05:16.740
<i>Luffy-san!</i>

00:05:25.650 --> 00:05:27.420
Roronoa Zoro!

00:05:28.820 --> 00:05:30.490
So cool!

00:05:31.790 --> 00:05:34.400
Move and you're dead.

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:36.190
Too scary!

00:05:40.230 --> 00:05:43.370
I'll be a pirate.
I promise you that.

00:05:43.370 --> 00:05:47.110
I'm officially a criminal,
now that I've fought the navy.

00:05:47.110 --> 00:05:49.680
But I'll tell you this right now.

00:05:49.680 --> 00:05:52.410
<i>I'm only going to
fulfill my ambition!</i>

00:05:52.410 --> 00:05:53.650
Ambition?

00:05:53.650 --> 00:05:56.980
To be the world's
greatest swordsman!

00:05:56.980 --> 00:06:00.190
If I wind up having
to give that up,

00:06:00.190 --> 00:06:04.530
you'd better accept responsibility
and apologize to me!

00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:08.060
The world's greatest swordsman?
That sounds great!

00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:12.530
The King of the Pirates would need
no less than that on his crew!

00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:13.900
You sure talk big.

00:06:13.900 --> 00:06:16.700
At this point, whether it's as
a criminal or whatever else,

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:19.640
<i>I will spread my name
throughout the world!</i>

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:24.310
What're you standing around for?!
Slaughter them this instant!

00:06:25.310 --> 00:06:27.920
Duck, Zoro!

00:06:27.920 --> 00:06:32.180
Gum-Gum Whip!

00:06:34.420 --> 00:06:37.160
Y-you did it! Incredible!

00:06:37.160 --> 00:06:39.330
What the hell are you?

00:06:39.330 --> 00:06:42.260
I ate the Gum-Gum Fruit.

00:06:42.260 --> 00:06:43.900
Gum-Gum Fruit?

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:45.400
A rubber person!

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:47.940
<i>So he does have
Devil Fruit powers!</i>

00:06:47.940 --> 00:06:50.270
Captain! We don't stand
a chance against them!

00:06:50.270 --> 00:06:51.740
These guys are crazy!

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:54.070
We can't even handle
Zoro by himself!

00:06:56.610 --> 00:06:58.410
This is a direct order!

00:06:58.410 --> 00:07:00.250
Everyone who spouted
weakness just now...

00:07:00.250 --> 00:07:02.250
...must now shoot themselves
in the head!

00:07:02.250 --> 00:07:05.280
I have no need for
weakling soldiers!

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:11.290
These troops are mental!

00:07:11.290 --> 00:07:12.620
<i>Luffy-san!</i>

00:07:14.630 --> 00:07:17.620
Crush this navy!

00:07:26.070 --> 00:07:30.880
Rankless, low-status bums have
no right whatsoever to defy me!

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:34.780
I am Navy Captain
"Axe-Hand" Morgan!

00:07:34.780 --> 00:07:37.580
I'm Luffy!
Nice to meetcha!

00:07:37.580 --> 00:07:39.580
Die!

00:07:48.900 --> 00:07:50.630
T-the captain!

00:07:50.630 --> 00:07:53.100
R-runt...

00:07:55.200 --> 00:07:57.200
Die!

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:58.540
No thanks!

00:08:01.210 --> 00:08:03.040
C-Captain Morgan is...

00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:06.910
...being trounced completely...

00:08:08.750 --> 00:08:10.280
And you call yourself a navy?!

00:08:10.280 --> 00:08:12.950
You've destroyed Coby's dream!

00:08:13.950 --> 00:08:17.150
<i>Hold it, Straw Hat!
Check this out!</i>

00:08:18.930 --> 00:08:21.700
I said hold it!
Are you stupid?!

00:08:21.700 --> 00:08:24.870
Pay attention!
I have a hostage here!

00:08:24.870 --> 00:08:26.600
<i>Helmeppo-sama!</i>

00:08:26.600 --> 00:08:27.930
Hey.

00:08:29.540 --> 00:08:32.370
If you value this guy's life,
don't move!

00:08:32.370 --> 00:08:35.370
One move and I'll shoot!

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:46.990
<i>Luffy-san! I don't want
to get in your way!</i>

00:08:46.990 --> 00:08:48.320
Even if it means dying!

00:08:48.320 --> 00:08:50.720
Yeah, I know!

00:08:50.720 --> 00:08:52.730
Give it up, stupid son!

00:08:52.730 --> 00:08:55.060
Coby really is ready to die!

00:08:56.230 --> 00:08:57.400
Don't move!

00:08:57.400 --> 00:09:00.230
I told you not to move!
I-I'll shoot!

00:09:01.240 --> 00:09:02.540
Behind you!

00:09:02.540 --> 00:09:03.870
Gum-Gum...

00:09:03.870 --> 00:09:09.440
I am Navy Captain
"Axe-Hand" Morgan!

00:09:09.440 --> 00:09:14.710
--Dad! Kill him, quick!
--...Pistol!

00:09:17.250 --> 00:09:18.580
Nice!

00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:29.230
Zoro.

00:09:29.230 --> 00:09:31.890
My pleasure, Captain.

00:09:39.740 --> 00:09:41.280
Captain Morgan's been beaten!

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:43.610
--Unbelievable!
--These guys are insane!

00:09:45.250 --> 00:09:48.910
If anyone else still wants
to catch us, come forward!

00:09:52.090 --> 00:09:55.620
--Hurray!
--We're free!

00:09:55.620 --> 00:09:58.060
--Yahoo!
--Morgan's reign is over!

00:09:58.060 --> 00:10:00.530
Hurray for the navy!

00:10:00.530 --> 00:10:04.530
Huh? Everyone's happy their
captain's been beaten...

00:10:04.530 --> 00:10:07.970
Everyone was just
afraid of Morgan!

00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:15.440
<i>What's wrong, Zoro-san?!
Are you hurt?!</i>

00:10:15.440 --> 00:10:17.970
I'm... hungry...

00:10:22.880 --> 00:10:25.050
Sorry!

00:10:25.050 --> 00:10:27.040
Just endure it
for a while!

00:10:41.840 --> 00:10:44.500
Doesn't seem to be in here,
either...

00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:04.490
Yes! A chart of
the Grand Line!

00:11:04.490 --> 00:11:06.620
I knew they had one!

00:11:07.730 --> 00:11:09.260
"I've flashily taken the map! Buggy"

00:11:09.260 --> 00:11:12.100
"I've flashily taken the map! Buggy"
T-this isn't a chart!
What is this mark?!

00:11:12.100 --> 00:11:12.260
T-this isn't a chart!
What is this mark?!

00:11:14.770 --> 00:11:16.670
Captain Buggy...

00:11:17.670 --> 00:11:21.010
The man known
as Buggy the Immortal...

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.140
I'm stuffed!

00:11:52.140 --> 00:11:54.470
I was definitely at my rope's end,

00:11:54.470 --> 00:11:56.810
having not eaten for three weeks!

00:12:00.150 --> 00:12:03.520
Huh? You're finished already?

00:12:03.520 --> 00:12:06.550
How the heck can you have
a bigger appetite than me?!

00:12:06.550 --> 00:12:09.320
It tastes good! Right, Coby?

00:12:09.320 --> 00:12:12.390
Thank you for treating
me to food, too...

00:12:12.390 --> 00:12:15.730
<i>It's no problem! The town
has been saved, after all!</i>

00:12:15.730 --> 00:12:18.300
You really are amazing!

00:12:18.300 --> 00:12:21.370
Yep, I am! And I'm gonna
be even more amazing!

00:12:21.370 --> 00:12:24.240
'Cause I'm gonna be
King of the Pirates!

00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:26.240
And I even have a crew!

00:12:26.240 --> 00:12:29.870
So, how many others have you
gathered besides me?

00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:35.580
You said you were in the
middle of gathering a crew.

00:12:35.580 --> 00:12:37.480
To be King of the Pirates,

00:12:37.480 --> 00:12:40.120
you must have
a good number gathered.

00:12:40.120 --> 00:12:40.890
Just you.

00:12:40.890 --> 00:12:43.420
Huh?! Then...

00:12:43.420 --> 00:12:45.790
Yep! Just us two!

00:12:45.790 --> 00:12:48.200
We're gonna call just
us two a pirate crew?!

00:12:48.200 --> 00:12:50.630
<i>What's wrong with that?
We are strong!</i>

00:12:50.630 --> 00:12:53.670
What about a ship?
Where's your pirate ship?

00:12:53.670 --> 00:12:55.030
There.

00:13:01.640 --> 00:13:02.780
<i>That?</i>

00:13:02.780 --> 00:13:06.440
<i>We'll have a ship this big
before long!</i>

00:13:08.420 --> 00:13:09.880
And how's that?!

00:13:09.880 --> 00:13:12.380
And I'd like a pirate flag, too!

00:13:19.630 --> 00:13:22.600
Yeah! Yeah, yeah! So cool!

00:13:22.600 --> 00:13:27.500
<i>I think Luffy-san was born
without any sense of planning.</i>

00:13:27.500 --> 00:13:30.840
Did I really make this
guy my captain?!

00:13:30.840 --> 00:13:34.010
Well, we'll get more
crew members before long!

00:13:34.010 --> 00:13:38.250
Hey, hey! Where are you guys
gonna go to now?

00:13:38.250 --> 00:13:41.840
Isn't it obvious?!
The Grand Line!

00:13:43.120 --> 00:13:45.350
You still only have
two members!

00:13:45.350 --> 00:13:47.390
There's no way you
can go there!

00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:48.420
No way! No way! No way!

00:13:48.420 --> 00:13:52.030
Is the Grand Line that
terrible of a place?

00:13:52.030 --> 00:13:53.790
Naturally!

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:58.230
You know this world
has two oceans, right?

00:13:58.230 --> 00:14:02.800
And the giant continent that cuts
them right in two is the Red Line.

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:06.070
Supposedly, there's a town right
in the middle of the Red Line,

00:14:06.070 --> 00:14:10.540
and the Grand Line goes
through it at a right angle...

00:14:10.540 --> 00:14:14.050
...and stretches around the world.

00:14:14.050 --> 00:14:17.250
It was said that Gold Roger,
King of the Pirates,

00:14:17.250 --> 00:14:20.050
once obtained everything
this world has to offer,

00:14:20.050 --> 00:14:26.990
and before he died, he said he left
the great One Piece treasure there,

00:14:26.990 --> 00:14:30.930
so pirates everywhere have since
set sail for the Grand Line!

00:14:30.930 --> 00:14:36.600
It's now an intense battlefield,
and even called a pirate graveyard!

00:14:40.810 --> 00:14:43.440
I've heard from patrons before...

00:14:43.440 --> 00:14:47.980
...that whoever enters the Grand
Line never comes out alive...

00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:51.490
But the One Piece
is somewhere there,

00:14:51.490 --> 00:14:53.150
so we're going there!

00:14:53.150 --> 00:14:54.890
Guess it can't be helped!

00:14:54.890 --> 00:14:56.560
<i>Not you too, Zoro-san?!</i>

00:14:56.560 --> 00:14:58.690
What's it matter?
You're not going, are you?

00:14:58.690 --> 00:15:02.030
N-no, but I'm worried
about you!

00:15:02.030 --> 00:15:03.830
Is that so wrong?!

00:15:03.830 --> 00:15:06.830
<i>Luffy-san and I haven't
known each other long,</i>

00:15:06.830 --> 00:15:08.570
<i>but we are friends!</i>

00:15:08.570 --> 00:15:10.040
Right?

00:15:10.040 --> 00:15:13.970
Yeah! We're gonna part ways,
but we'll always be friends!

00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:21.310
Since I was little kid,
I've never had friends...

00:15:21.310 --> 00:15:25.290
Much less anyone who would
fight for my sake...

00:15:25.290 --> 00:15:28.950
But more than anything, I never
tried to fight for anything...

00:15:31.090 --> 00:15:36.330
But you two taught me how
to live for my beliefs!

00:15:36.330 --> 00:15:39.770
I've decided to make
my childhood dream come true!

00:15:39.770 --> 00:15:41.500
I want to join the navy!

00:15:41.500 --> 00:15:45.170
Shouldn't you be more
worried about yourself, then?

00:15:46.540 --> 00:15:48.410
Even if you were
just a chore boy,

00:15:48.410 --> 00:15:51.940
<i>you did spend two years
on Alvida's pirate ship.</i>

00:15:53.950 --> 00:15:56.750
Don't underestimate the navy's
info-gathering skills.

00:15:56.750 --> 00:15:59.950
If they find out about that,
you'll never get to join.

00:15:59.950 --> 00:16:02.180
N-now that you mention it...

00:16:03.190 --> 00:16:04.850
Pardon me!

00:16:09.900 --> 00:16:12.970
Is it true that you are pirates?!

00:16:12.970 --> 00:16:18.440
Yeah. We gained a member
and became a pirate group just now!

00:16:18.440 --> 00:16:23.610
We appreciate that you saved our base
and this town from that tyrant!

00:16:23.610 --> 00:16:26.510
However, now that we know
you are pirates,

00:16:26.510 --> 00:16:29.180
in the name of the navy,
we cannot stand by quietly!

00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:34.750
You will leave this town at once!

00:16:34.750 --> 00:16:38.530
Out of obligation, we will refrain
from contacting headquarters.

00:16:38.530 --> 00:16:41.290
Hey, navy guy!
How can you talk like that?!

00:16:41.290 --> 00:16:45.100
Even you guys were subdued
and terrified of Morgan!

00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:48.370
We owe these people our lives!

00:16:48.370 --> 00:16:49.700
Yeah! Yeah!

00:16:53.370 --> 00:16:55.540
Well, guess we should go!

00:16:55.540 --> 00:16:57.310
Thanks for the food, lady!

00:16:57.310 --> 00:17:00.180
You guys are leaving already?

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:01.510
Yeah.

00:17:08.690 --> 00:17:10.460
Aren't you part of their crew?

00:17:10.460 --> 00:17:12.530
Eh? I...

00:17:12.530 --> 00:17:13.860
I'm...

00:17:18.100 --> 00:17:19.430
Hold it!

00:17:19.430 --> 00:17:21.870
Well? Is he?!

00:17:21.870 --> 00:17:25.870
I know what he's done until now.

00:17:25.870 --> 00:17:28.380
<i>Luffy-san! You wouldn't!</i>

00:17:28.380 --> 00:17:31.140
There was this reaaally
fat pirate lady,

00:17:31.140 --> 00:17:33.350
I think her name was Ahiruda.

00:17:33.350 --> 00:17:35.380
<i>Luffy-san!</i>

00:17:35.380 --> 00:17:37.650
<i>If they find out I was
on a pirate ship,</i>

00:17:37.650 --> 00:17:40.420
<i>I'll never get
to join the navy!</i>

00:17:40.420 --> 00:17:45.830
And she had this iron club.
Man, she was an ugly hag!

00:17:45.830 --> 00:17:49.700
And for two whole years,
this guy was her-

00:17:49.700 --> 00:17:54.360
<i>Please don't!
Please don't, Luffy-san!</i>

00:18:03.010 --> 00:18:05.180
Now you've done it,
you bastard!

00:18:05.180 --> 00:18:07.840
Damn you!
Damn you! Damn you!

00:18:10.450 --> 00:18:11.950
Stop that!

00:18:11.950 --> 00:18:15.890
We won't allow you to cause
any more trouble in this town!

00:18:15.890 --> 00:18:19.380
Hey! You've gone too far.
That's enough.

00:18:25.730 --> 00:18:28.370
It's very clear that you
guys aren't crewmates!

00:18:28.370 --> 00:18:30.860
Now leave this town at once!

00:18:37.310 --> 00:18:38.800
<i>On purpose...</i>

00:18:40.610 --> 00:18:42.950
<i>He did that on purpose...</i>

00:18:46.650 --> 00:18:49.060
<i>For me...</i>

00:18:49.060 --> 00:18:52.390
<i>He purposely got me riled up
to make me hit him...</i>

00:18:54.130 --> 00:18:59.120
<i>Even in the very end,
I wound up relying on him!</i>

00:19:02.500 --> 00:19:05.670
<i>Nothing's changed at all!</i>

00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:10.480
<i>Am I an idiot?!</i>

00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:12.610
Please!

00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:15.720
Please...
let me join the navy!

00:19:15.720 --> 00:19:18.950
I'll gladly do chores
or anything else!

00:19:18.950 --> 00:19:21.290
If it means I can be marine!

00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:27.760
Lieutenant Colonel!
I'm against the idea!

00:19:27.760 --> 00:19:30.460
I still don't fully
trust this kid!

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:34.070
<i>There have been cases of marines
being pirate spies!</i>

00:19:34.070 --> 00:19:37.070
We'll first need to conduct
a background check...

00:19:37.070 --> 00:19:40.400
<i>I'm a man who will become
a navy officer!</i>

00:19:50.620 --> 00:19:53.720
Countless comrades of ours
have been killed by pirates.

00:19:53.720 --> 00:19:56.760
Don't take the navy lightly.

00:19:56.760 --> 00:19:57.760
Then...

00:19:57.760 --> 00:19:59.750
Permission to join granted!

00:20:01.630 --> 00:20:02.960
Yes, sir!

00:20:09.370 --> 00:20:11.600
"I've flashily taken the map! Buggy"

00:20:15.310 --> 00:20:17.480
That was a pretty lame act.

00:20:17.480 --> 00:20:19.850
Wouldn't be shocked
if they saw through it.

00:20:19.850 --> 00:20:23.420
Coby'll handle the rest on
his own now. I just know it.

00:20:23.420 --> 00:20:25.190
It's a nice way to leave,
though.

00:20:25.190 --> 00:20:27.850
Being unable to turn back
'cause everyone hates you-

00:20:27.850 --> 00:20:30.460
it's pirate-like!

00:20:30.460 --> 00:20:31.520
That's true!

00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:32.860
<i>Luffy-san!</i>

00:20:35.260 --> 00:20:40.030
Thank you! I'll never forget
all you've done for me!

00:20:40.030 --> 00:20:43.900
<i>I've never heard of a pirate
being thanked by a marine...</i>

00:20:46.910 --> 00:20:49.880
Let's meet again sometime, Coby!

00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:53.180
<i>--Luffy-san...
--Bye!</i>

00:20:53.180 --> 00:20:55.410
All hands, salute!

00:20:58.590 --> 00:21:02.090
See ya!

00:21:02.090 --> 00:21:04.320
That's a great friend
you have there.

00:21:09.960 --> 00:21:10.990
Yes, sir!

00:21:12.230 --> 00:21:16.670
Our salute just now is
in violation of naval law!

00:21:16.670 --> 00:21:20.670
Therefore, we will all go without
food for three days! Understood?!

00:21:20.670 --> 00:21:22.010
Yes, sir!

00:21:25.010 --> 00:21:26.350
<i>I'm sure...</i>

00:21:26.350 --> 00:21:30.020
<i>I'm sure we'll meet again
sometime, somewhere, Luffy-san!</i>

00:21:30.020 --> 00:21:34.490
<i>Even if we're divided
as pirates and marines...</i>

00:21:34.490 --> 00:21:37.150
<i>...let's meet again someday!</i>

00:21:41.860 --> 00:21:45.470
Alright! Our pirate crew
finally sets sail!

00:21:45.470 --> 00:21:48.230
Looks like some pretty good
adventures'll be waiting for us.

00:21:51.640 --> 00:21:54.300
<i>I will be King of the Pirates!</i>

00:21:57.140 --> 00:22:01.310
You really seem obsessed about
this King of the Pirates thing.

00:22:01.310 --> 00:22:02.980
Is there some sorta reason for it?

00:22:02.980 --> 00:22:05.490
No reason. It's just...

00:22:05.490 --> 00:22:06.720
It's just?

00:22:06.720 --> 00:22:10.390
I swore to a certain man that...

00:22:10.390 --> 00:22:12.660
...someday I would gather a great crew,

00:22:12.660 --> 00:22:14.660
find the world's greatest treasure,

00:22:14.660 --> 00:22:16.650
and become
King of the Pirates!

00:22:22.670 --> 00:22:24.830
This straw hat knows!

00:22:26.810 --> 00:22:28.140
I see...

00:22:37.180 --> 00:22:39.590
Alright! Let's go!

00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:43.920
Set sail for the Grand Line!

00:22:56.070 --> 00:23:06.070
<i>When I was little, I had
a vision of a treasure map</i>

00:23:10.280 --> 00:23:17.220
<i>and I always searched
for that miraculous place</i>

00:23:17.220 --> 00:23:24.390
<i>before someone else
could beat me to it</i>

00:23:26.930 --> 00:23:36.930
<i>If the world is going to change</i>

00:23:38.410 --> 00:23:45.420
<i>before I can even attain my dream</i>

00:23:45.420 --> 00:23:52.490
<i>then take me to the time
when I knew nothing</i>

00:23:52.490 --> 00:24:02.490
<i>so that my memories won't fade</i>
